      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ORGANISED CRIME (8) flew the lids and led throughout to get off the mark with his maiden win, then finished a half a length second last start at Bendigo over 425m (23.68). Boxed wide here. Racing well and looks a leading chance again. PAW WINDER (2) looks close to another win after finishing third last time (30.29) in a Mix 6/7 FIN at this track. Strong form has emerged from his last run. Overdue and is among the main hopes. LITTLE RAT (1) recorded her best time this course and distance latest, finishing a 7 length second behind Indy Melmen in 30.21. Has the ability and can measure up. TASTE (5) can measure up with the right run.",
